Package: GeneScoreR
Title: Gene Scoring from Count Tables
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Aris", "Syntakas", , "sejjsyn@ucl.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: GeneScoreR is an R package that automatically calculates gene scores from gene count tables, providing two methods for scoring: the z-score method, which requires a table of samples being scored and a count table, and the geometric mean method, which does not rely on control samples.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
